		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><a href="https://www.mikekohn.net/micro/naken_asm.php" class="postlink">https://www.mikekohn.net/micro/naken_asm.php</a><br /><br />Stumbled on this today looking for an STM8 assembler for linux.  Was surprised to see it supports practically every mcu core I could think of.  It also has releases for all most operating systems.  On top of that it's also actively under development and seeking feedback.  Figured I'd share it here as it's mentioned as a way to help their effort.  I'm looking forward to trying it out and hoping it turns out to be my assember swiss army knife.  I couldn't find any mention of it here on nesdev, curious if anyone here has heard anything about it or tried it out yet.

		

